What you need to know:

China is owed about $145 billion in Africa, making it the biggest bilateral lender.In Kenya, it is owed some $5 billion, and rating agency Moody’s rated Ghana, Angola and Kenya as countries facing credit risks this year.In April, the International Monetary Fund approved a $500 million fund to cancel half a year of debt owed by 25 countries. Nineteen of them were from Africa and would benefit from the IMF’s Catastrophe Containment and Relief Trust (CCRT) to address the impact of the Covid-19 pandemic.